         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">5. 9. [189]3 ¶ Dear Baron von Mueller, ¶  ¶ I have made very careful inquiry and find that there is not the slightest grounds for believing that a cart was taken by Leichhardt on his final journey. ¶ ...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">93.09.05</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">From James Thomson</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">OM 65-21/1, letterbook of James Park Thomson, pp. 337-8, John Oxley Library, State Library of Queensland, Brisbane.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">5. 9. [189]3<note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                     <seg style="font-style: italic; ">editorial addition.</seg>
                  </p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Dear Baron von Mueller,</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I have made very careful inquiry and find that there is not the slightest grounds for believing that a cart was taken by Leichhardt on his final journey.<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>See M to A. Macdonald, 25 September 1893.</p>
               </note> Mr […] says emphatically that a cart <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">was</hi>
               </seg> […]<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">The MS page has become friable and a line of text has crumbled away.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>You are now on the eve of the Adelaide Meeting of the Association.<note xml:id="ftn4" type="footnote" n="4">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>The Australasian Association for the Advancement of Science met in Adelaide, 25 September-2 October 1893.</p>
               </note> We were led to [be]lieve that the meeting following the Adelaide one was to be held in Brisbane in 1894, but now at the last moment our local secretary<note xml:id="ftn5" type="footnote" n="5">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>J. Shirley.</p>
               </note> has raised so many obstacles to the former arrangement that it has been decided by the casting vote of our chairman at our last meeting, who is [to] induce the Adelaide people to agree to the Brisbane meeting for 1895. I can see no reason for leaving it so [late] &amp; I objected to the arrangement [on] the grounds of it being contrary to the Rules of the Association [which] imply that the meetings shall be <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">annual</hi>
               </seg>. My objection was supported by half of our meeting, &amp; it was only on the <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">casting vote</hi>
               </seg> of the Chairman that the date was fixed for 1895. I trust you will advise your scientific [friends] to insist on 1894 as the year of the Brisbane meeting &amp; that you will yourself urge it in fairness to the other colonies, who are waiting, a visit from the Association.<note xml:id="ftn6" type="footnote" n="6">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>In the event, the Brisbane meeting was held in January 1895.</p>
               </note> Kindly regard this advice &amp; information as <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">strictly private</hi>
               </seg> &amp; <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">confidential</hi>
               </seg>.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">Very faithfully yours</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>J. P. Thomson</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Baron Sir F. von Mueller</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">K.C.M.G., F.R.S., etc., etc.,</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Melbourne</p>
